[
  {
    "text": "Imagine this:",
    "start": 6.908,
    "duration": 1.868
  },
  {
    "text": "You're fast asleep",
    "start": 8.8,
    "duration": 1.608
  },
  {
    "text": "when all of a sudden you're awoken!",
    "start": 10.432,
    "duration": 2.306
  },
  {
    "text": "And not by your alarm clock.",
    "start": 12.762,
    "duration": 1.694
  },
  {
    "text": "Your eyes open,",
    "start": 14.48,
    "duration": 1.219
  },
  {
    "text": "and there's a demon sitting on your chest,",
    "start": 15.723,
    "duration": 2.041
  },
  {
    "text": "pinning you down.",
    "start": 17.788,
    "duration": 1.561
  },
  {
    "text": "You try to open your mouth and scream,",
    "start": 19.373,
    "duration": 1.81
  },
  {
    "text": "but no sound comes out.",
    "start": 21.207,
    "duration": 1.448
  },
  {
    "text": "You try to get up and run away,",
    "start": 22.679,
    "duration": 1.595
  },
  {
    "text": "but you realize that you\nare completely immobilized.",
    "start": 24.298,
    "duration": 3.045
  },
  {
    "text": "The demon is trying to suffocate you,",
    "start": 27.367,
    "duration": 2.17
  },
  {
    "text": "but you can't fight back.",
    "start": 29.561,
    "duration": 1.935
  },
  {
    "text": "You've awoken into your dream,",
    "start": 31.52,
    "duration": 2.125
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's a nightmare.",
    "start": 33.669,
    "duration": 2.137
  },
  {
    "text": "It sounds like a Stephen King movie,",
    "start": 35.83,
    "duration": 2.299
  },
  {
    "text": "but it's actually a medical condition",
    "start": 38.153,
    "duration": 1.762
  },
  {
    "text": "called sleep paralysis,",
    "start": 39.939,
    "duration": 1.734
  },
  {
    "text": "and about half of the population",
    "start": 41.697,
    "duration": 1.524
  },
  {
    "text": "has experienced this strange phenomenon",
    "start": 43.245,
    "duration": 1.858
  },
  {
    "text": "at least once in their life.",
    "start": 45.127,
    "duration": 1.645
  },
  {
    "text": "This panic-inducing episode",
    "start": 46.796,
    "duration": 2.045
  },
  {
    "text": "of coming face-to-face with the creatures",
    "start": 48.865,
    "duration": 1.953
  },
  {
    "text": "from your nightmares",
    "start": 50.842,
    "duration": 1.259
  },
  {
    "text": "can last anywhere from seconds to minutes",
    "start": 52.125,
    "duration": 2.228
  },
  {
    "text": "and may involve visual\nor auditory hallucinations",
    "start": 54.377,
    "duration": 3.028
  },
  {
    "text": "of an evil spirit",
    "start": 57.429,
    "duration": 1.574
  },
  {
    "text": "or an out-of-body feeling\nlike you're floating.",
    "start": 59.027,
    "duration": 2.757
  },
  {
    "text": "Some have even mistaken sleep paralysis",
    "start": 61.808,
    "duration": 1.858
  },
  {
    "text": "for an encounter with a ghost",
    "start": 63.69,
    "duration": 1.843
  },
  {
    "text": "or an alien abduction.",
    "start": 65.557,
    "duration": 2.484
  },
  {
    "text": "In 1867, Dr. Silas Weir Mitchell",
    "start": 68.065,
    "duration": 3.702
  },
  {
    "text": "was the first medical professional",
    "start": 71.791,
    "duration": 1.67
  },
  {
    "text": "to study sleep paralysis.",
    "start": 73.485,
    "duration": 2.465
  },
  {
    "text": "\"The subject awakes to consciousness",
    "start": 75.974,
    "duration": 2.016
  },
  {
    "text": "of his environment",
    "start": 78.014,
    "duration": 1.244
  },
  {
    "text": "but is incapable of moving a muscle.",
    "start": 79.282,
    "duration": 2.495
  },
  {
    "text": "Lying to all appearance, still asleep.",
    "start": 81.801,
    "duration": 2.795
  },
  {
    "text": "He's really engaged\nfor a struggle for movement,",
    "start": 84.62,
    "duration": 2.921
  },
  {
    "text": "fraught with acute mental distress.",
    "start": 87.565,
    "duration": 2.575
  },
  {
    "text": "Could he but manage to stir,",
    "start": 90.164,
    "duration": 1.892
  },
  {
    "text": "the spell would vanish instantly.\"",
    "start": 92.08,
    "duration": 2.483
  },
  {
    "text": "Even though Dr. Mitchell was the first",
    "start": 94.587,
    "duration": 1.81
  },
  {
    "text": "to observe patients in a state\nof sleep paralysis,",
    "start": 96.421,
    "duration": 2.432
  },
  {
    "text": "it's so common that nearly every culture",
    "start": 98.877,
    "duration": 2.12
  },
  {
    "text": "throughout time has had some kind",
    "start": 101.021,
    "duration": 1.572
  },
  {
    "text": "of paranormal explanation for it.",
    "start": 102.617,
    "duration": 2.634
  },
  {
    "text": "In medieval Europe, you might\nthink that an incubus,",
    "start": 105.275,
    "duration": 3.201
  },
  {
    "text": "a sex-hungry demon in male form,",
    "start": 108.5,
    "duration": 2.205
  },
  {
    "text": "visited you in the night.",
    "start": 110.729,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "In Scandinavia, the mare,",
    "start": 112.388,
    "duration": 2.58
  },
  {
    "text": "a damned woman,",
    "start": 114.992,
    "duration": 1.105
  },
  {
    "text": "is responsible for visiting sleepers",
    "start": 116.121,
    "duration": 1.842
  },
  {
    "text": "and sitting on their rib cages.",
    "start": 117.987,
    "duration": 2.481
  },
  {
    "text": "In Turkey, a jinn holds you down",
    "start": 120.492,
    "duration": 2.321
  },
  {
    "text": "and tries to strangle you.",
    "start": 122.837,
    "duration": 2.113
  },
  {
    "text": "In Thailand, Phi Am bruises\nyou while you sleep.",
    "start": 124.974,
    "duration": 3.368
  },
  {
    "text": "In the southern United States,",
    "start": 128.366,
    "duration": 1.484
  },
  {
    "text": "the hag comes for you.",
    "start": 129.874,
    "duration": 2.159
  },
  {
    "text": "In Mexico, you could blame",
    "start": 132.057,
    "duration": 1.277
  },
  {
    "text": "subirse el muerto,\nthe dead person, on you.",
    "start": 133.358,
    "duration": 3.308
  },
  {
    "text": "In Greece, Mora sits upon your chest",
    "start": 136.69,
    "duration": 1.987
  },
  {
    "text": "and tries to asphyxiate you.",
    "start": 138.701,
    "duration": 2.143
  },
  {
    "text": "In Nepal, Khyaak the ghost",
    "start": 140.868,
    "duration": 1.826
  },
  {
    "text": "resides under the staircase.",
    "start": 142.718,
    "duration": 2.082
  },
  {
    "text": "It may be easier to blame",
    "start": 145.483,
    "duration": 1.191
  },
  {
    "text": "sleep paralysis on evil spirits",
    "start": 146.698,
    "duration": 1.847
  },
  {
    "text": "because what's actually\nhappening in your brain",
    "start": 148.569,
    "duration": 2.239
  },
  {
    "text": "is much harder to explain.",
    "start": 150.832,
    "duration": 1.974
  },
  {
    "text": "Modern scientists believe\nthat sleep paralysis",
    "start": 152.83,
    "duration": 2.191
  },
  {
    "text": "is caused by an abnormal overlap",
    "start": 155.045,
    "duration": 1.708
  },
  {
    "text": "of the REM, rapid eye movement,",
    "start": 156.777,
    "duration": 2.058
  },
  {
    "text": "and waking stages of sleep.",
    "start": 158.859,
    "duration": 1.89
  },
  {
    "text": "During a normal REM cycle,",
    "start": 160.773,
    "duration": 2.216
  },
  {
    "text": "you're experiencing\na number of sensory stimuli",
    "start": 163.013,
    "duration": 2.533
  },
  {
    "text": "in the form of a dream,",
    "start": 165.57,
    "duration": 1.406
  },
  {
    "text": "and your brain is unconscious\nand fully asleep.",
    "start": 167.0,
    "duration": 2.889
  },
  {
    "text": "During your dream,",
    "start": 169.913,
    "duration": 1.402
  },
  {
    "text": "special neurotransmitters are released,",
    "start": 171.339,
    "duration": 2.182
  },
  {
    "text": "which paralyze almost all of your muscles.",
    "start": 173.545,
    "duration": 2.558
  },
  {
    "text": "That's called REM atonia.",
    "start": 176.127,
    "duration": 2.013
  },
  {
    "text": "It's what keeps you\nfrom running in your bed",
    "start": 178.164,
    "duration": 2.096
  },
  {
    "text": "when you're being chased in your dreams.",
    "start": 180.284,
    "duration": 2.052
  },
  {
    "text": "During an episode of sleep paralysis,",
    "start": 182.36,
    "duration": 2.469
  },
  {
    "text": "you're experiencing\nnormal components of REM.",
    "start": 184.853,
    "duration": 2.885
  },
  {
    "text": "You're dreaming and your muscles\nare paralyzed,",
    "start": 187.762,
    "duration": 2.205
  },
  {
    "text": "only your brain is conscious\nand wide awake.",
    "start": 189.991,
    "duration": 2.729
  },
  {
    "text": "This is what causes you to imagine",
    "start": 192.744,
    "duration": 1.266
  },
  {
    "text": "that you're having an encounter",
    "start": 194.034,
    "duration": 1.477
  },
  {
    "text": "with a menacing presence.",
    "start": 195.535,
    "duration": 1.531
  },
  {
    "text": "So this explains the hallucinations,",
    "start": 197.09,
    "duration": 2.735
  },
  {
    "text": "but what about the feelings of panic,",
    "start": 199.849,
    "duration": 1.798
  },
  {
    "text": "strangling,",
    "start": 201.671,
    "duration": 0.891
  },
  {
    "text": "choking,",
    "start": 202.586,
    "duration": 0.794
  },
  {
    "text": "chest pressure",
    "start": 203.404,
    "duration": 0.734
  },
  {
    "text": "that so many people describe?",
    "start": 204.162,
    "duration": 2.05
  },
  {
    "text": "Well during REM,",
    "start": 206.935,
    "duration": 1.155
  },
  {
    "text": "the function that keeps you",
    "start": 208.114,
    "duration": 0.835
  },
  {
    "text": "from acting out your dreams,",
    "start": 208.973,
    "duration": 1.657
  },
  {
    "text": "REM atonia,",
    "start": 210.654,
    "duration": 1.394
  },
  {
    "text": "also removes voluntary control",
    "start": 212.072,
    "duration": 1.776
  },
  {
    "text": "of your breathing.",
    "start": 213.872,
    "duration": 1.145
  },
  {
    "text": "Your breath becomes more shallow",
    "start": 215.041,
    "duration": 1.852
  },
  {
    "text": "and rapid.",
    "start": 216.917,
    "duration": 0.924
  },
  {
    "text": "You take in more carbon dioxide",
    "start": 217.865,
    "duration": 1.477
  },
  {
    "text": "and experience a small\nblockage of your airway.",
    "start": 219.366,
    "duration": 2.829
  },
  {
    "text": "During a sleep paralysis episode,",
    "start": 222.219,
    "duration": 2.356
  },
  {
    "text": "a combination of your body's fear response",
    "start": 224.599,
    "duration": 2.149
  },
  {
    "text": "to a perceived attack by an evil creature",
    "start": 226.772,
    "duration": 2.135
  },
  {
    "text": "and your brain being wide awake",
    "start": 228.931,
    "duration": 1.785
  },
  {
    "text": "while your body is in an REM sleep state",
    "start": 230.74,
    "duration": 2.449
  },
  {
    "text": "triggers a response for you\nto take in more oxygen.",
    "start": 233.213,
    "duration": 2.991
  },
  {
    "text": "That makes you gasp",
    "start": 236.228,
    "duration": 1.53
  },
  {
    "text": "for air,",
    "start": 237.782,
    "duration": 1.012
  },
  {
    "text": "but you can't",
    "start": 238.818,
    "duration": 1.012
  },
  {
    "text": "because REM atonia",
    "start": 239.854,
    "duration": 1.013
  },
  {
    "text": "has removed control of your breath.",
    "start": 240.891,
    "duration": 2.626
  },
  {
    "text": "This struggle for air\nwhile your body sleeps",
    "start": 243.541,
    "duration": 2.096
  },
  {
    "text": "creates a perceived sensation",
    "start": 245.661,
    "duration": 1.403
  },
  {
    "text": "of pressure on the chest",
    "start": 247.088,
    "duration": 1.673
  },
  {
    "text": "or suffocation.",
    "start": 248.785,
    "duration": 2.172
  },
  {
    "text": "While a few people experience",
    "start": 250.981,
    "duration": 1.381
  },
  {
    "text": "sleep paralysis regularly",
    "start": 252.386,
    "duration": 1.587
  },
  {
    "text": "and it may be linked to sleep disorders",
    "start": 253.997,
    "duration": 1.858
  },
  {
    "text": "such as narcolepsy,",
    "start": 255.879,
    "duration": 1.184
  },
  {
    "text": "many who experience\nan episode of sleep paralysis",
    "start": 257.087,
    "duration": 2.464
  },
  {
    "text": "do so infrequently,",
    "start": 259.575,
    "duration": 1.643
  },
  {
    "text": "perhaps only once in a lifetime.",
    "start": 261.242,
    "duration": 2.348
  },
  {
    "text": "So you can rest easy,",
    "start": 263.614,
    "duration": 1.246
  },
  {
    "text": "knowing that an evil entity is not trying",
    "start": 264.884,
    "duration": 2.47
  },
  {
    "text": "to haunt,",
    "start": 267.378,
    "duration": 0.405
  },
  {
    "text": "possess,",
    "start": 267.807,
    "duration": 0.441
  },
  {
    "text": "strangle,",
    "start": 268.272,
    "duration": 0.463
  },
  {
    "text": "or suffocate you.",
    "start": 268.759,
    "duration": 1.685
  },
  {
    "text": "Save that for the horror films!",
    "start": 270.468,
    "duration": 2.09
  }
]